---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="API reference"
  description="feedbackmonk public API — submit feedback, fetch widget config, query the public roadmap, vote, promote. JWT semantics included."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>API reference</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      A thin REST surface over JSON. Public endpoints are unauthenticated
      (or optionally JWT-bearer); admin endpoints require a session cookie
      from <code>POST /api/v1/auth/login</code>. Wire shapes are stable as
      of v1.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section aria-labelledby="auth-heading">
    <h2 id="auth-heading">Authentication</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Public endpoints:</strong> optional
      <code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;jwt&gt;</code>. The JWT is verified
      against the project's registered public key; the verified claim is
      stored alongside the submission. No JWT &rarr; anonymous submission
      (paired with the <code>X-Feedbackmonk-Anon-Cookie</code> first-party
      cookie for group-by-browser).
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Admin endpoints:</strong> session cookie (<code>feedbackmonk_session</code>)
      issued by <code>POST /api/v1/auth/login</code>. All admin endpoints
      are tenant-scoped &mdash; you only ever see rows belonging to your
      tenant (DEC-FBR-03, enforced by the
      <em>multi-tenant-isolation-check</em> Verification Oracle).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="widget-endpoints-heading">
    <h2 id="widget-endpoints-heading">Widget endpoints</h2>

    <h3>GET /api/v1/projects/&#123;project_id&#125;/widget-config</h3>
    <p>
      Public. Returns the widget's render configuration (Contract C12):
      brand text, allowed auth modes, submission kinds, body length cap.
    </p>

    <h3>POST /api/v1/projects/&#123;project_id&#125;/feedback</h3>
    <p>Public. Submits one feedback row. Request body:</p>
    <pre><code>{`{
  "kind": "bug" | "feature" | "question" | "other",
  "subject": "Short title (1-200 chars)",
  "body":    "Free-form body (1-16384 chars)",
  "email":   "optional@reply-to.example"
}`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      Returns <code>201 Created</code> with the generated
      <code>FB-XXXXXX</code> id. Cap-firing (Free tier, &gt;50 in rolling
      month) returns <code>402 Payment Required</code> with a typed
      <code>TierCapExceededBody</code>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="roadmap-endpoints-heading">
    <h2 id="roadmap-endpoints-heading">Public roadmap endpoints</h2>
    <p>
      Public; no auth required. Anonymous voters are deduplicated via the
      first-party cookie.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>GET    /api/v1/projects/&#123;project_id&#125;/roadmap</code> &mdash; list, paginated.</li>
      <li><code>GET    /api/v1/projects/&#123;project_id&#125;/roadmap/top-voted</code> &mdash; sorted by vote count.</li>
      <li><code>GET    /api/v1/projects/&#123;project_id&#125;/roadmap/items/&#123;slug&#125;</code> &mdash; single item.</li>
      <li><code>POST   /api/v1/projects/&#123;project_id&#125;/roadmap/items/&#123;slug&#125;/vote</code> &mdash; cast a vote.</li>
      <li><code>DELETE /api/v1/projects/&#123;project_id&#125;/roadmap/items/&#123;slug&#125;/vote</code> &mdash; retract.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="admin-endpoints-heading">
    <h2 id="admin-endpoints-heading">Admin endpoints</h2>
    <p>
      Session-cookie authenticated. Tenant-scoped by the
      <code>feedbackmonk-repository</code> layer &mdash; the API does no
      raw SQL.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>GET  /api/v1/admin/feedback</code> &mdash; list, status/kind filterable.</li>
      <li><code>GET  /api/v1/admin/feedback/&#123;id&#125;</code> &mdash; detail with replies + status history.</li>
      <li><code>POST /api/v1/admin/feedback/&#123;id&#125;/transition</code> &mdash; status flow with required reply.</li>
      <li><code>POST /api/v1/admin/feedback/&#123;id&#125;/reply</code> &mdash; attach a typed reply (queues email).</li>
      <li><code>POST /api/v1/admin/feedback/&#123;id&#125;/promote</code> &mdash; promote to public roadmap (Q24 invariant: body verbatim, no submitter attribution).</li>
      <li><code>GET  /api/v1/admin/tier</code> &mdash; current tier + per-resource usage vs cap (Contract C17).</li>
      <li><code>GET, POST, PATCH /api/v1/admin/projects/&#123;project_id&#125;/roadmap[…]</code> &mdash; manage roadmap items + slug.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="errors-heading">
    <h2 id="errors-heading">Error shapes</h2>
    <p>
      All errors are JSON with a stable
      <code>error</code> code and a human <code>message</code>:
    </p>
    <pre><code>{`{ "error": "tier_cap_exceeded", "message": "...", "resource": "feedback_in_rolling_month", "current": 50, "limit": 50 }`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      The <code>tier_cap_exceeded</code> body shape is Contract C18 &mdash;
      stable across tiers and resources, parseable client-side without
      string scraping.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="health-heading">
    <h2 id="health-heading">Health</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><code>GET /health</code> &mdash; liveness; always 200 if the process is up.</li>
      <li><code>GET /health/ready</code> &mdash; readiness; 200 when DB is reachable, 503 otherwise. Use this for orchestrator probes (the self-host compose stack relies on it).</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header { margin-block: 2rem 1.5rem; }
  pre { max-width: 100%; }
</style>
